title: Patient 597 Core Set (custom panel)
characteristics_ch1.8: Time (yrs) from RRP to first rising PSA: 3.30732375085558
characteristics_ch1.10: Time (yrs) from RRP to second rising PSA: 4.50650239561944
characteristics_ch1.12: Time (yrs) from PSA recurrence to systemic disease: 0.736481861738535
extract_protocol_ch1: Four freshly cut 10 micron sections of FFPE tissue were deparaffinized and the Gleason dominant cancer focus was macrodissected. RNA was extracted using the High Pure RNA Paraffin Kit from Roche (Indianapolis, IN).
label_protocol_ch1: cy3, cy5 labeling was performed in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions
hyb_protocol: hybridization was performed in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions
scan_protocol: Arrays were scanned using Illumina's BeadArray Reader
data_processing: Illumina's Bead Studio Software using no normalization was used to process the image files. The raw data was then normalized using cyclic loess (fastlo). The normalized value for the probes was averaged to determine the expression level for the gene. The DASL method labels each sample with a mixture of CY3 and Cy5. Only a single sample is applied to each array.  The scanner measures fluorescence of both Cy3 and Cy5.  This data is contained in the red and grn files for each sample. The bead studio software averages the red and green signals to provide a single value for the expression of a particular probe.

characteristics_ch1.10: Time (yrs) from RRP to second rising PSA: 2.26420260095825
characteristics_ch1.12: Time (yrs) from PSA recurrence to systemic disease: 2.56810403832991
extract_protocol_ch1: Four freshly cut 10 micron sections of FFPE tissue were deparaffinized and the Gleason dominant cancer focus was macrodissected. RNA was extracted using the High Pure RNA Paraffin Kit from Roche (Indianapolis, IN).
label_protocol_ch1: cy3, cy5 labeling was performed in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions
hyb_protocol: hybridization was performed in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions
scan_protocol: Arrays were scanned using Illumina's BeadArray Reader
data_processing: Illumina's Bead Studio Software using no normalization was used to process the image files. The raw data was then normalized using cyclic loess (fastlo). The normalized value for the probes was averaged to determine the expression level for the gene. The DASL method labels each sample with a mixture of CY3 and Cy5. Only a single sample is applied to each array.  The scanner measures fluorescence of both Cy3 and Cy5.  This data is contained in the red and grn files for each sample. The bead studio software averages the red and green signals to provide a single value for the expression of a particular probe.

The normalized value for the probes was averaged to determine the expression level for the gene. The DASL method labels each sample with a mixture of CY3 and Cy5. Only a single sample is applied to each array.  The scanner measures fluorescence of both Cy3 and Cy5.  This data is contained in the red and grn files for each sample. The bead studio software averages the red and green signals to provide a single value for the expression of a particular probe.
